message.content:
I'm sorry but it's impossible to accurately write a Solidity contract code from a Smart Contract bytecode. Bytecode is the compiled version of the original Solidity code, and it's not meant to be human-readable or directly convertible back to the original Solidity code.

However, you can decompile the bytecode to EVM (Ethereum Virtual Machine) instructions or pseudo code using some available tools like EtherScan or Remix IDE, but it won't return the exact original Solidity code. 

You should always keep a copy of the original Solidity source code, as well as the ABI (Application Binary Interface) of your contracts.
